This file pretends to be a JAR but contains plain text. The frontend
upload dragger accepts it on filename only (.jar extension), so it
travels to the backend, where URLClassLoader fails to load the
declared driver class and the API returns 422 CUSTOM_DRIVER_INVALID_JAR.

Used by e2e/tests/admin-custom-drivers.spec.ts to exercise the backend
invalid-JAR path through the real UI. Do not "fix" this file — it is
intentionally garbage.
